.SH NAME
i3c_master_add_i3c_dev_locked \- add an I3C slave to the bus
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i3c_master_add_i3c_dev_locked
.BI "(struct i3c_master_controller *master "  ","
.BI "u8 addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "master" 12
master used to send frames on the bus
.IP "addr" 12
I3C slave dynamic address assigned to the device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is instantiating an I3C device object and adding it to the
I3C device list. All device information are automatically retrieved using
standard CCC commands.

The I3C device object is returned in case the master wants to attach
private data to it using \fBi3c_dev_set_master_data\fP.

This function must be called with the bus lock held in write mode.
.SH "RETURN"
a 0 in case of success, an negative error code otherwise.
